This paper deals with the problem of multi-label classification using decision trees. The paper proposes a novel algorithm for constructing and training multi-label decision trees with logarithmic-depth. This problem is related to machine learning and data mining, which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as it covers the theoretical and algorithmic aspects of machine learning. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as it covers the broader field of AI, which includes machine learning. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another possible category as multi-label classification is often used in image and video analysis. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as decision trees are a common data structure used in machine learning. Finally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also possible as multi-label classification is used in natural language processing tasks such as text classification.
